com.bluegosling.collections

Class LockFreeLinkedBlockingQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
        • com.bluegosling.collections.AbstractLockFreeBlockingQueue<E>
          • com.bluegosling.collections.LockFreeLinkedBlockingQueue<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element stored in the queue
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, BlockingQueue<E>, Queue<E>

    public class LockFreeLinkedBlockingQueue<E>
extends AbstractLockFreeBlockingQueue<E>
    A lock-free implementation of BlockingQueue, backed by a ConcurrentLinkedQueue.

    Unlike the ConcurrentLinkedQueue that backs it, this blocking queue provides an O(1) implementation of size(). An AtomicInteger is used to track the size and to also ensure that any configured capacity limit is enforced.

    This class handles blocking operations (e.g. AbstractLockFreeBlockingQueue.take(), AbstractLockFreeBlockingQueue.put(Object), etc.) with custom wait queues instead of using Locks and Conditions.

    Use of Iterator.remove() is discouraged. If invoked and there are multiple, equal values in the queue, the first one will be removed instead of the one last fetched by the iterator.
